description:
an interview with jazz legend
          Bobby Hutcherson

i had the very great fotune of meeting and playing with bobby hutcherson during the time i lived there in the bay area in the 1980's. an even greater honor was to meet dr. jackie mclean while i was a student in connecticut in the19 70's. bobby is another of the legacy masters to hail from los angeles and is an unbelievibly approachable and beautiful human being. 

this interview is from 2002 at north sea jazz festival; conduted by myself. it is about a person who is pinnacle in the lives of so many of todays jazz practicioners, jaclie mclean...

happy birthday bobby hutcherson...you are one of the nicest people i ever met....gba
title: Aquarian Vibes on Jackie Mclean
